KG name: AMOn+: Cultural Variations in Interpersonal Communication Ontology
Description: We present Activity Model Ontology(AMOn+)- an ontology suite- which is developed by an international and multi-disciplinary team using a theory-driven approach to conceptualise cultural variations in interpersonal communication for augmenting user-generated content. Specifically we have utilised established theories on culture to provide base knowledge structure to the conceptualization. For extending the base structure and to achieve more concrete conceptualization- we have utilized DBpedia.
Sources: Web:Absent Name:Dhavalkumar Thakker; Stan Karanasios; Emmanuel G. Blanchard; Vania Dimitrova; Lydia Lau Email:d.thakker@leeds.ac.uk
